Set up a system of equations in which x represents the cost of a sombrero in $\ $$ and y represents the cost of a pair of flip-flops in $\$$ .</think>
\begin{align}x + y = 32\\ x + z = 42\\ y + z = 30\\ \end{align}
<answer>\\ 
  Subtract the first equation from the second and the third.
  \begin{align}
x + y - (x + z) &= 32 - 30 \\
x + z &= 42 \\
y + z &= 30 \\
y &= 22
\end{align}
  \begin{align}x + y &= 32\\x + 22 &= 32\\x &= 10\end{align}
  The cost of a pair of flip-flops is $\$22$ and the sombrero costs $\$10$.</answer>

